<p>Wednesday 16.8.16<br/>Quiet as usual, rained slightly,  Paid 40 Francs, &pound;1.8.8</p>
<p>Thursday 17.8.16<br/>Still raining, roads very muddy.<br/>Received letters &amp; parcels from home.  Had a look over a fine old church in Doulieu a few days back, which was completely burnt out by the Germans, with the use of petroleum.</p>
<p>Friday 18.8.16<br/>A &amp; B Sec came here route marching this morning, appear to be getting a rough time with squad drill again.</p>
<p>Saturday 19.8.16<br/>Rained hard during morning.  Dozens of Tommies come here direct from Somme &amp; look much the worse for their experience; they tell some very appaling tales of the Slaughter</p>
